pub fn gc_major(&mut self, roots: &mut [FzValue], mailbox: &mut VecDeque<FzValue>) {
  // from_ranges = [(young_start, young_top), (old_start, old_top)] — both generations.
  // Allocate fresh old block (sized by last_major_live_bytes*2 or bytes_used()).
  // Cheney BFS from roots into fresh old block — same algorithm as current gc().
  // pool_free(old_start, old_size_class)  // reclaim old from-space
  // pool_free(young_start, young_size_class)  // reclaim young (all promoted or dead)
  // Install fresh block as new old block. Reset young_top = young_start (young now empty).
  // Set gc_watermark = young_start + young_size*3/4 (young watermark unchanged).
  // Update last_major_live_bytes. Reset minor_gc_count = 0.
}

This is the existing gc() with two from_ranges instead of one. The Cheney machinery (cheney_forward, cheney_trace_children, forward_field) is unchanged. The to-space is a fresh old block; the young block is reset rather than freed (reused as the new young space).

Tests: after major GC, all live objects (from both young and old) are in the new old block; both old from-space and young from-space are freed; young block is empty and ready for allocation; last_major_live_bytes = bytes in new old block; minor_gc_count = 0.
